b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":58,"category_name":"Updates","pr_category_id":"2","title_name":"Update Notification[Addendum]","message":"<div>The update to version 1.1.2 will be made available <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1540782000\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div>An automatic update is scheduled to occur at approximately <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1540868400\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>A Tenfold Summon Voucher will be sent as a gift to players as a thank-you for updating to the latest version. This message will be updated when the gifts are sent out.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Version 1.1.2 introduces additional features around the new event, as well as fixes to some issues. See below for details.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Details:<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0New features\/adjustments:<\/div><div>The following features and changes have been implemented.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe limit for getherwings will be increased from 6 to 12, with the maximum able to be held at one time increased from 50 to 99.<\/div><div>\\u30fbDuring raid battles, adventurer AI has been adjusted to perform more offensively.<\/div><div>Note: This will not apply to non-raid battle quests.<\/div><div>\\u30fbGuests in raid events can now receive a chance to participate in an Extra Battle after clearing an Expert Raid.<\/div><div>\\u30fbDuring weapon crafting, a message will now be displayed when a weapon needs to be unbound.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIt now takes less time before an adventurer can move after performing a dash attack.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Auto function now carries over into the next quest.<\/div><div>Note: It will be reset when the game is restarted or when beginning a co-op game.<\/div><div>\\u30fbCamera distance adjustments made during gameplay are maintained.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen using the optimize feature to optimize adventurers with the Adventurers (under Apply To) option checked, weapons and dragons that match the adventurers&#39; elements will be given priority.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen using the optimize feature to optimize adventurers with the All (under Element) option checked, weapons and dragons that match the adventurers&#39; elements will be given priority.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe amount and types of upgrade materials used when choosing Auto to upgrade weapons and dragons have been optimized.<\/div><div>\\u30fbTapping and holding the Castle button at the bottom of the screen will take you directly to the castle grounds.<\/div><div>\\u30fbAI adventurers will move toward treasure chests when the Auto feature is enabled.<\/div><div>\\u30fbStat bonuses gained from equipping weapons, dragons, and characters with matching elements are now calculated into your team&#39;s Might.<\/div><div>\\u30fbRequired might is now a condition to take part in raid events.<\/div><div>Note: This will be reflected beginning with the Kindness and Captivity raid event.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Campaign Updates <span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1540978200\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><br>The presentation of the following Campaign chapters has been updated.<br>\\u30fbCh. 5\/3-3 The Channeling Chamber<br>\\u30fbCh. 5\/4-1 Zethia<br>\\u30fbCh. 6\/4-4 Diadem of Light<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Issues fixed:<\/div><div>The following issues have been fixed:<\/div><div>\\u30fbTapped facilities would sometimes immediately become deselected.<\/div><div>\\u30fbTapping and holding the Castle icon at the bottom of the screen on certain menus would cause the game to stop responding.<\/div><div>\\u30fbDetailed information on helpers&#39; stats was not being correctly reflected at the start of quests.<\/div><div>\\u30fbAttempting to switch to the Upgrade menu while transitioning to other menus would sometimes result in an error.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe message &quot;recommended might&quot; was mistakenly displayed instead of &quot;required might&quot; at the start of quests in which your required might was too low.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIt sometimes would become impossible to progress in mana circles.<\/div><div>\\u30fbPerforming certain steps in a mana circle would sometimes cause the game to become unresponsive at the load screen.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIn the Helper Settings menu, the details screen for your chosen adventurer was not displaying the skill level.<\/div><div>\\u30fbDuring co-op play, Zodiark would sometimes stop moving after a guest would give up.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIn the matching screen for co-op play, ability and element-buff values were not being reflected on the adventurer-information screen.<\/div><div>\\u30fbStatus-down effects were being amplified too much when certain adventurers used skills during co-op play.<\/div><div>(Update to ver. 1.1.2 is required for all the members in the co-op room.)<\/div><div>\\u30fbErrors would sometimes occur when determining how much time was required to recover getherwings.<\/div><div>\\u30fbAdventurers recovering from stun as a result of Verica&#39;s skill could not perform normal attacks, dash attacks, force strikes, and dodges.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIn the Pending Requests menu, accepting or denying requests from the bottom of the screen would cause the list&#39;s display to become corrupted.<\/div><div>\\u30fbWhen looking at the detail screen for your friends&#39; adventurers, their equipment was not being displayed.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIn the Graphic Settings menu, selecting Good or Sharp was making Force Strikes difficult to perform.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe English language display was displaying line breaks in the middle of certain words.<\/div><div>\\u30fbQuests shown on the tips screens were displaying the incorrect suggested might.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe facility level was not taking the smithy level into account when trying to level the smithy.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Notes:<\/div><div>It may take time for the update information to be reflected in the store.<\/div><div>Users may not be able to perform the update due to their device&#39;s data cache being full.<\/div><div>If you are unable to perform the update, restart your device, wait a few minutes, and then attempt the download from the store.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>To be added <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1540868400\\"><\/span><\/strong><\/span><br>The following will be sent to players who started the game by <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1540868400\\"><\/span>:<br><br>\\u30fbTenfold Summon Voucher x1<br><br>This will be sent to your goodie box when you log in, and you can claim it until <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1541473140\\"><\/span>. This is seven days after it&#39;s sent to your goodie box.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1540890000\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><br>The following update was added to the list of new features\/adjustments.<br>\\u30fbStat bonuses gained from equipping weapons, dragons, and characters with matching elements are now calculated into your team&#39;s Might.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1540985400\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><\/div><div>The following issue was not correctly fixed in update 1.1.2. We have removed it from the list of fixed issues.<br>\\u30fbThe Sort by Element + Ascending order in the Friend List was not functioning correctly.<br>We will be fixing this issue in a future update.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost!<\/div>","start_time":1540811700,"prev_article_id":"38","next_article_id":"89","image_path":"","update_time":1542363776}}}'